{
  "stem": "10283.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 16.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I got into a little hotel because I didn't want to stay on the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] station.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they woke me up, and I went by myself then at 4:00 or 5:00 in the-- to the train and got on the train.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "All of a sudden, there come two big SS men on the train and started to brag what wonderful things had just happened.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Did you see how the synagogues are burning?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Did you see all that glass all over?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "How the people smash the store windows?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we got so many people, and we beat them up, and they were-- and I was sitting there, 15 years old, all alone and shivering, and not knowing what's going to happen to my parents and how I'm going to come.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when I came to Breslau about 2:00 in the early afternoon, the-- the station, I took a trolley car to station.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the-- the street passes-- almost passes by the synagogue, and the synagogue was still burning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I saw the synagogue burning, and I saw all that glass on the-- on the street.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had quite a number of Jewish stores and businesses on the main streets.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was scared.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I came home, and nobody was home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So-- but finally my mother came home, and she told me that my father had been hiding at my widowed grandmother, because the SS went to all Jewish homes and grabbed the men.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they didn't go to the-- you know, my grandmother lived alone at that time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they were-- my grandfather and my father were hiding there at this [? thing. ?] And they were spared.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were not taken.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
